@startuml
title SOMA Rust Native LoRA Training Pipeline

actor CLI as "Command Line Interface"
participant Config as "Config System"
participant Dataset as "Dataset Loader"
participant Preprocessor as "VAE Preprocessor"
participant Segmenter as "SAM/YOLOv8 via ORT"
participant MaskUtils as "Mask Transformation"
participant Model as "UNet/Transformer + T-LoRA"
participant Loss as "Semantic Weighted + Attn Penalty"
participant Optimizer as "Prodigy Optimizer"
participant Checkpoint as "Safetensors Saver"
participant Logger as "Metrics & Node UI"

CLI -> Config : Load training configuration
CLI -> Dataset : Request batch
Dataset -> Preprocessor : Encode images -> latent tensors
Preprocessor --> Dataset : Return latent tensors

Dataset -> Segmenter : Forward images through segmentation models
Segmenter --> MaskUtils : Return segmentation masks
MaskUtils --> Dataset : Downsample & broadcast masks to latent shape

Dataset -> Model : Forward latent tensors + conditioning
Model -> Loss : Predicted noise & attention maps
MaskUtils -> Loss : Provide semantic weight tensors
Loss -> Model : Compute weighted & attention-penalty loss
Loss -> Optimizer : Calculate gradients with tiered backward pass
Optimizer -> Model : Update model weights
Optimizer -> Logger : Log metrics

Model -> Checkpoint : Save model weights periodically
Checkpoint -> Logger : Record checkpoint info

CLI -> Logger : Display progress, optional node-graph view

@enduml